==English==

===Etymology 1===
Euphemistic term for "God", dating back to the 18th century. Possibly a compaction of "God's body".
(Compare the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_minced_oaths#God | List of minced oaths].)

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɒli|-ɒli]]

===Alternative forms===
*[[by goles]]!

====Interjection====
'''golly!'''
# {{cattag|Euphemisms}}: God!

===Etymology 2===
Shortened from [[golliwog]]
====Noun====
#  A type of black stuffed doll
# ''(offensive):'' a dark skinned person, not necessarily a negro

===Etymology 3===
Possibly from [[Goliath]]
====Verb====
#''(Australian juvenile):'' to spit

====Noun====
#''(Australian juvenile):'' chewing gum
#''(Australian juvenile):'' saliva or phlegm: hack up a golly

====Derived terms====
*[[Golly pot]]

